cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper focuses on task-oriented dialogue systems, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) that falls under cs.CL.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed framework uses deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of AI that falls under cs.AI.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses Seq2Seq models, which are a type of neural network commonly used in NLP and fall under cs.LG.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the design and implementation of a dialogue system, which falls under cs.SD.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper mentions improving user experience and relieving people from tedious works, which falls under cs.HC.
